headline: US Stock Market Today: S&P 500 Futures Edge Higher As Jobs Stay Firm, Yields Ease
summary: The Morning Bull - US Market Morning Update Wednesday, Feb, 25 2026 US stock futures are pointing slightly higher this morning, with E-mini S&P 500 contracts up about 0.1%, as investors weigh stronger US hiring, lower long term interest rates and a softer housing market. ADP data show private employers adding an average of 12,750 jobs per week over the past month, which hints that paychecks and consumer spending are still holding up.
